        <abstract>
            <p>In London yesterday for Vivisection Commission.</p> 
<p>Is revising his chapter on Pangenesis [in <hi rend="italic">Variation</hi>, 2d ed.] to allow that gemmules probably multiply in the reproductive organs.</p> 
            <p>Notes examples of inheritance of acquired characteristics cited by Brown-Séquard.</p>
            <p>Doubts that double parentage is necessary for complex organisations.</p>
        </abstract>
